er";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:23;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"Alex King: Hiring: Web Application UI/UX Designer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"http://alexking.org/?p=14342";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://alexking.org/blog/2012/09/04/hiring-web-application-uiux-designer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1789:"<p>We&#8217;re still in the process of filling the <a href="http://alexking.org/blog/2012/08/09/hiring-devs-project-manager-denver">three positions I posted about previously</a> (technical project manager, front-end web developer and full-stack web developer), but we&#8217;ve just added another position that I&#8217;m really excited about. We are looking for someone to join our team specifically as a UI/UX lead for web applications.</p>\n<p>We do a bunch of different stuff at <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com">Crowd Favorite</a> and we care deeply about creating great products with great user experiences. Part of that user experience is the admin-side of the CMS, web app, etc. We are building ambitious WordPress sites for well known clients, and want to make sure their experience managing their site is as awesome as the experience that the users of their site have.</p>\n<p>We also create our own products &#8211; some WordPress related, some internal, some just as fun projects. We want to make the interfaces for those sing as well. I think this is a terrific opportunity to work with a top-notch team that knows how to execute and won&#8217;t compromise on vision or UX/UI experience.</p>\n<p>Think you&#8217;re right right person for the job? Can&#8217;t wait to <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com/jobs/">hear from you</a>.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m also very proud to be advertising this position on the excellent <a href="http://www.randsinrepose.com/onejob-jobs.html">Rands in Repose website</a> as part of his <a href="http://www.randsinrepose.com/archives/2012/08/12/one_job.html">One Job</a> sponsorship. I&#8217;ve known Michael for a long time, and I&#8217;m thrilled to be in a position to be able to support his excellent work and present this opportunity to his audience.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 04 Sep 2012 19:35:06 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Alex";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:24;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"Joseph: WordCamp SLC (Utah) 2012 Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"https://josephscott.org/?p=6364";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://josephscott.org/archives/2012/09/wordcamp-slc-utah-2012-update/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:734:"<p>Quick update on the upcoming <a href="http://2012.slc.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp SLC 2012</a> on September 22nd:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://2012.slc.wordcamp.org/schedule/">schedule</a> for the day is now live</li>\n<li>early bird pricing has ended, but we still have <a href="http://2012.slc.wordcamp.org/registration/">general admission tickets</a>, with the still reasonable cost of $20</li>\n<li><a href="http://2012.slc.wordcamp.org/2012/09/04/shirt-orders-go-in-tomorrow/">t-shirt order is going in tomorrow</a> so if you want to be assured a of shirt in your size you&#8217;ll need to register before the end of the day on September 5th.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Look forward to seeing everyone again on the 22nd up at the UoU campus.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 04 Sep 2012 16:34:26 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Joseph Scott";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:25;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Weblog Tools Collection: How not to Design a Theme from Drew Strojny";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=11902";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/0QhwP_MTbl0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1141:"<p><a href="http://wordpress.org">WordPress</a> 3.5 has entered early development and <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2012/03/23/twenty-twelve-moved-to-3-5/">will be featuring</a> the new Twenty Twelve default theme.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re curious about what went into the new default theme, designer <a href="http://drewstrojny.com">Drew Strojny</a> took a reverse approach to this in his talk at <a href="http://2012.sf.wordcamp.org">WordCamp San Francisco 2012</a>, <a href="http://wordpress.tv/2012/08/31/drew-strojny-how-not-to-design-a-default-theme/">How not to Design a Default Theme</a>.</p>\n<div id="v-zxcUHtZZ-1" class="video-player"></div>\n<p>Currently, <a href="http://theme.wordpress.com/themes/twentytwelve/">Twenty Twelve is available to WordPress.com bloggers</a> if you want to play around with it. It will also be available via <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/themes/">the official Theme Directory</a> for WordPress.org bloggers shortly, and included with the release of WordPress 3.5.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/0QhwP_MTbl0" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 04 Sep 2012 15:15:09 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"James";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"WordPress.tv: Helen Hou-Sandi: Making Custom Content Management Disappear into the WordPress Admin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i