at compulsively seeks to innovate, disrupt and ultimately solve some issue or demand in our society, (even ones we&#8217;re not yet aware of).  The &#8230; <a href="http://time.ly/feature-event-grow-big-or-grow-home/">Continued</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Evan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5017:"<p><a href="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/clip_image001.jpeg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-5802" title="clip_image001" src="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/clip_image001-282x300.jpeg" alt="" width="282" height="300" /></a>Perhaps you&#8217;ve already heard but Timely is a &#8220;<em>start-up&#8221; </em>one of those fascinating creatures of modern business that compulsively seeks to innovate, disrupt and ultimately solve some issue or demand in our society, (even ones we&#8217;re not yet aware of).  The issue we seek to solve is the one of <em>event search and discovery,</em> namely how to help people find all the events happening in their given area and help people/businesses/organizations publish and connect events more easily.  After all, how we perceive our time is very much tied to the quality of the experiences we have with it and being fully aware of all the experiences available to us gives us the opportunity for that magical outcome of <em>time well spent</em>, and if we&#8217;re lucky even <em>the</em> <em>time of our lives. </em></p>\n<p>Having the time of our lives is exactly what we plan on doing this week at <a href="http://growconf.com/">GROW </a><a href="http://growconf.com/">Conference</a> (<a href="https://twitter.com/#!/search/%23growconf">#GROWconf</a>) in Vancouver, one of North America&#8217;s (nay the world&#8217;s!) premier events for start-up culture, industry and dialogue.</p>\n<div><a href="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/happening_1339783300.jpeg"><img class="size-full wp-image-5804 alignright" title="happening_1339783300" src="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/happening_1339783300.jpeg" alt="" width="250" height="200" /></a>This is the sort of place where deals are made, funding can be found, partnerships ignite and small companies make the inroads they need to become BIG companies. It&#8217;s a place of networking for sure but it&#8217;s also a place of growth, real entrepreneurial growth not just in funding opportunities but in terms of intellectual evolution for what it means to be a successful start-up in today&#8217;s world of dynamic technology and design.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>So much happens at this one event that it can be a little overwhelming; conferences (of course), seminars, guest speakers, workshops, tours, launches, after-parties, kite boarding! It&#8217;s a wonderland of entrepreneurial activity and spirit and this week it&#8217;s our <strong>feature event</strong>, not because we happen to be there or that it happens to be centered around the very nature of our business but because it exemplifies what we consider <em>a life changing event. </em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><a href="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/Screen-Shot-2012-08-21-at-1.23.15-PM.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-5809" title="Screen Shot 2012-08-21 at 1.23.15 PM" src="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/Screen-Shot-2012-08-21-at-1.23.15-PM-e1345580608856-300x277.png" alt="" width="240" height="222" /></a></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>When you put so many <a href="http://growconf.com/sessions/?id=6#talks">great thinkers</a> and status quo shakers into a few <a href="http://growconf.com/venue/">city blocks of downtown Vancouver</a>, something magical happens, actually lots of little magical things happen to many different people in many different places. An entrepreneur or perhaps a budding one, may enter as one thing and come out another. It&#8217;s transformative and we happen to think that a truly great event should lead you to indelible experiences that shape you or your ideas in some transformative way.</div>\n<div>\n<p>This year at GROW we hope to be transformed and we hope to transform. We&#8217;re looking to share <a href="http://time.ly/event-search-calendar/">our ideas</a> about how events should be published and discovered online and we&#8217;re hoping those very ideas evolve in the process of sharing them.</p>\n<p>This week at Grow you can find Timely CEO <a href="https://twitter.com/riklogtenberg">Rik Logtenberg</a> and Timely co-founder and VP Community <a href="https://twitter.com/BradleyRoulston">Bradley Roulston</a> strutting their stuff down the busy conference halls and happy-hour pow-wows. If you want to talk the future of event search and publishing please get in touch:</p>\n<div class="pull-left">Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/riklogtenberg">@Hubrik</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/IMG_4239_reasonably_small.jpeg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-5805" title="IMG_4239_reasonably_small" src="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/IMG_4239_reasonably_small.jpeg" alt="" width="128" height="128" /></a></div>\n<div class="pull-left">Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/BradleyRoulston#">@BradleyRoulston</a></p>\n<p><a style="color: #005580; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/2397c8b.jpeg"><img title="2397c8b" src="http://time.ly/wp-timely/assets/2397c8b.jpeg" alt="" width="128" height="128" /></a></div>\n</div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://time.ly/feature-event-grow-big-or-grow-home/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://